body_html:
@martinwicke

Thanks for the help. I've installed python 2.7 in an anaconda environment, exported PYTHON_BIN_PATH to point to the python in the environment and rerun everything, but I still don't see any changes in git. See log below:

(tf_dev_py2) alex@ubuntu:~/tensorflow$ export PYTHON_BIN_PATH="/home/alex/anaconda3/envs/tf_dev_py2/bin/python"
(tf_dev_py2) alex@ubuntu:~/tensorflow$ bazel build tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test --incompatible_load_argument_is_label=false --local_resources 4096,.5,1.0
WARNING: /home/alex/tensorflow/tensorflow/core/BUILD:1795:1: in includes attribute of cc_library rule //tensorflow/core:framework_headers_lib: '../../external/nsync/public' resolves to 'external/nsync/public' not below the relative path of its package 'tensorflow/core'. This will be an error in the future. Since this rule was created by the macro 'cc_header_only_library', the error might have been caused by the macro implementation in /home/alex/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow.bzl:1086:30
WARNING: /home/alex/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/learn/BUILD:15:1: in py_library rule //tensorflow/contrib/learn:learn: target '//tensorflow/contrib/learn:learn' depends on deprecated target '//tensorflow/contrib/session_bundle:exporter': No longer supported. Switch to SavedModel immediately.
WARNING: /home/alex/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/learn/BUILD:15:1: in py_library rule //tensorflow/contrib/learn:learn: target '//tensorflow/contrib/learn:learn' depends on deprecated target '//tensorflow/contrib/session_bundle:gc': No longer supported. Switch to SavedModel immediately.
INFO: Analysed target //tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test (0 packages loaded).
INFO: Found 1 target...
Target //tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test up-to-date:
  bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test
INFO: Elapsed time: 0.528s, Critical Path: 0.00s
INFO: Build completed successfully, 1 total action
(tf_dev_py2) alex@ubuntu:~/tensorflow$ bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test --update_goldens True
s.s.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Ran 4 tests in 0.000s

OK (skipped=2)
(tf_dev_py2) alex@ubuntu:~/tensorflow$ git status
On branch master
Your branch is up-to-date with 'origin/master'.
nothing to commit, working directory clean
(tf_dev_py2) alex@ubuntu:~/tensorflow$

Any ideas?

Regards,

Alex
